{"questionId":"27207","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A student investigating the relationship between chemical reactions and temperature finds&nbsp;the Arrhenius equation on the internet.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p>This equation links a variable <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> with the temperature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> are positive&nbsp;constants and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Arrhenius equation predicts that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math> is a straight line.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Write down</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>(i)&nbsp; &nbsp;the gradient of this line in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>;</p>\n<p>(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept of this line in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>taking <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi></math> of both sides&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br>(i)&nbsp; &nbsp;so gradient is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br>(ii)&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-intercept is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>A</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The implied <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> and <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> can only be awarded if <strong>both</strong> correct answers are seen. Award zero if only one value is correct <strong>and</strong> no working is seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27207","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"(i) the gradient of this line in terms of c; (ii) the y-intercept of this line in terms of A.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.9—Log laws"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}